Number.isInteger
- Signature: Number.isInteger(value) -> boolean
- Parameter: value (any) — to be tested for integerness
- Returns: boolean

RangeError
- Constructor: new RangeError(message?: string) -> RangeError
- Usage: throw new RangeError('message')

TypeError
- Constructor: new TypeError(message?: string) -> TypeError
- Usage: throw new TypeError('message')

Recommended FizzBuzz API (concrete signatures):
- export function fizzbuzzArray(n: number): string[]
  - Validates: typeof n === 'number', Number.isInteger(n), n >= 1
  - Throws: TypeError on type mismatch, RangeError on out-of-range
  - Returns: Array of length n containing the sequence strings

- export function* fizzbuzzGenerator(n: number): IterableIterator<string>
  - Same validations as fizzbuzzArray
  - Behavior: yields each output string in sequence, allowing streaming consumption

